Added host-side per-listener channel routing: new ControlMessage.setChannelMode (host→client), HostSession.setClientMode now persists per-peerID mode and pushes to that client, ConnectedClient gained a `mode` field, host UI's ListenersCard renders each listener as a row with the same 4-chip Stereo/L/R/Muted picker so the host conducts the L+R stereo pair. Mode is re-pushed on reconnect via clientModes dict.